The development of the big data market in Russia will provide an economic effect of 2.9 trillion rubles in five years

05 Nov 2019, 11:30


The accumulated economic effect of the large-scale introduction of Big Data technologies in Russia may amount to 2.9 trillion rubles. Between 2019 and 2024. Such data are contained in the Big Data Strategy until 2024, which was presented in Moscow.

The document was developed by the Big Data Association (ABD) together with the consulting company The Boston Consulting Group with the involvement of a wide range of experts.
According to Anna Serebryanikova, ABD President, member of MegaFon’s board of directors, head of the Information Infrastructure ANO Digital Economy working group, the government and businesses have to complete eight key tasks to achieve this economic effect:

consent to several purposes of data use (remote provision of consent simultaneously to several purposes);
processing personal data without direct consent (for example, transfer to subsidiaries as part of the production process);
digitalization of state data relevant to big data (standardization of the collection, storage and processing of, for example, data such as medical data);
creation of a special regulatory environment within the framework of the R & D sandbox (involvement of regulators to reduce barriers for the subsequent deployment of products);
creation and maintenance of “data lakes” (a database of standardized data and technology libraries);
incentives for introducing big data technologies (subsidies, adoption of special support programs, venture and project financing);
project and technical personnel reserve (the formation of an expert pool for the development of competencies and assistance to traditional industries in the implementation of big data technologies);
industry trust in big data technologies (holding events to familiarize representatives of traditional industries with the potential of Big Data technology).

Maria Polikanova, Head of the ABD Strategic Committee, Managing Director of Sberbank, said that the contribution of Big Data technology to GDP could be from 0.3% to 1.8% by 2024 against 2019 (0.3% is a pessimistic scenario; 0.5 % - inactivity scenario; 1.2% - base scenario; 1.8% - positive scenario).
According to ADB, the big data market in Russia is currently estimated at 45 billion rubles, and its annual growth rate is 12% since 2015.
According to M. Polikanova, in the implementation of the basic scenario, the market growth in 2024 will be about 100 billion rubles.

Currently, the members of the ABD are Yandex, Mail.Ru Group, Sberbank, Gazprombank, Tinkoff Bank, MegaFon, Rostelecom, Vympelcom, oneFactor, QIWI, the Analytical Center under the Government of the Russian Federation .


